The paper discusses a new approach for detecting network attacks using a network-based intrusion detection system (NIDS). This falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and network security (cs.NI). The proposed approach involves the use of distributed agents and monitoring anomalous behavior, which could also fall under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and social networks (cs.SI). The paper also discusses the use of experiments and data analysis, which could fall under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
